item.title: CVE-2023-6258|2024-02-08T18:05:32.581Z -- n%2Fa -- pkcs11-provider
item.description: A security vulnerability has been identified in the pkcs11-provider, which is associated with Public-Key Cryptography Standards (PKCS#11). If exploited successfully, this vulnerability could result in a Bleichenbacher-like security flaw, potentially enabling a side-channel attack on PKCS#1 1.5 decryption.
